Armand Hug (December 6, 1910, New Orleans - March 19, 1977, New Orleans) was an American jazz pianist.
In 1926 he joined a band led by Harry Shields, then was a member of the New Orleans Owls in 1928.

He recorded for the first time in 1936, with Sharkey Bonano, though for his career he was known as a solo pianist.
